  <prompt>
    Close real-bug-ledger entry **RB-T070-03** by resolving the dead-path coverage gap in `AnalysisChatContextResolver`. The 7 affected tests were written against a stub path that returned a non-null default `AnalysisChatContextResponse` for any string `analysisId`; production removed the stub and now requires `Guid.TryParse(analysisId)` + a successful Dataverse retrieval, both of which fail in the in-process `CustomWebAppFactory`. So the tests assert behavior that no longer exists.

    🚨 **OWNER DECISION REQUIRED AT TASK START** — the ledger surfaces 2 viable paths (lines 573-577):

    1. **Restore stub for tests** (~2-4h): re-introduce a feature flag / test seam in `AnalysisChatContextResolver` so the unit-test factory can inject a fake that returns canned responses for `"analysis-stub-*"` IDs. Preserves the existing 7 tests with minimal change. Production path unaffected.
    2. **Wire a real Dataverse mock** (~6-8h): extend `CustomWebAppFactory` (with §4.5 owner approval) to mock `IDataverseEntityService.RetrieveAsync` returning synthetic `sprk_analysisoutput` / `sprk_analysisplaybook` rows. Removes stub dependency.

    The alternate resolution mode `archived-as-dead-target` (delete the 7 tests as documenting dead behavior) is ALSO viable if the owner judges the tests not worth restoring — production coverage continues via the AnalysisWorkspace Code Page integration tests + the 3 still-passing endpoint-mapping tests in the same class.

    Surface 🔔 **Human Input Required** with the 3 paths. Wait for owner ACK before implementing. Per NFR-04 cite `RB-T070-03` + chosen resolution mode (`repaired` OR `archived-as-dead-target`).
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent resolving a dead-path coverage gap; owner-decision-gated implementation across 3 paths.</role>

  <goal>
    EITHER `AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs` gains a test-seam stub (path 1; 7 tests Skip→Pass) OR `CustomWebAppFactory` gains a Dataverse mock (path 2; 7 tests Skip→Pass) OR the 7 tests are archived as dead-target (path 3; 0 tests flip). RB-T070-03 transitions to `repaired` (paths 1, 2) or `archived-as-dead-target` (path 3).
  </goal>

