  <context>
    <background>
      Per ledger §579-581: production traffic always sends real Dataverse-bound GUIDs against live data; the `AnalysisWorkspace` Code Page exercises the resolver end-to-end. The stub-resolver unit tests existed only to spot-check the endpoint mapping + response shape in unit isolation — which the 3 still-passing class members (`MapAnalysisChatContextEndpoints_MethodExists_AndIsStatic`, `GetAnalysisChatContext_WithoutAuth_ReturnsUnauthorized`, `GetAnalysisChatContext_WithAuth_DoesNotReturn404`) continue to cover at a coarser level. This is the load-bearing fact for path 3: integration coverage is intact.

      Path 1 (restore stub) is the lower-cost option and preserves the test contract. Path 2 (real mock) raises factory complexity but is closer to production behavior. Path 3 (archive) is the lowest-cost outcome but reduces unit-test surface area.
    </background>
