  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load RB-T070-03 ledger entry (lines 551-585 in real-bug-ledger.md). Confirm Status is `open` or `assigned-to-r2`.</step>
    <step order="2">🔔 **Human Input Required** — surface the 3 paths (restore stub / real mock / archive) with effort estimates + tradeoffs. Recommend path 1 (lowest cost, preserves unit-test surface). WAIT for owner ACK.</step>
    <step order="3">If path 1 (restore stub) chosen: read `AnalysisChatContextResolver.cs` `ResolveAsync` (line 127) + `ResolveFromDataverseAsync` (line 189). Add a test-seam: e.g., an `IAnalysisChatContextStub` interface (or feature flag via `IConfiguration`) that allows the factory to inject canned responses for `"analysis-stub-*"` prefixed IDs. Production behavior unchanged when stub not configured.</step>
    <step order="4">If path 2 (real mock) chosen: extend `CustomWebAppFactory` ConfigureServices to register a mock `IDataverseEntityService.RetrieveAsync` for `sprk_analysisoutput` + `sprk_analysisplaybook` entity types — requires §4.5 owner approval recorded BEFORE editing. Per ADR-010 NFR-03 do NOT add new DI registrations beyond the existing baseline.</step>
    <step order="5">If path 3 (archive) chosen: rename `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/AnalysisChatContextResolverTests.cs` (the 7 tests) → `AnalysisChatContextResolverTests.cs.archived-YYYY-MM-DD` per predecessor NFR-06. The 3 still-passing tests in the same file stay in their current location (or split out before archive if same file).</step>
    <step order="6">For paths 1/2: remove `Skip = "..."` + per-test traits on the 7 affected tests. For path 3: no test change (archived).</step>
    <step order="7">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="8">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~AnalysisChatContextResolver"`. For paths 1/2: confirm 7 tests pass + 3 existing tests remain green. For path 3: confirm 3 remaining tests still pass.</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify <50% line replacement; no new DI registrations (ADR-010 NFR-03); AI Chat stays in-process (ADR-013).</step>
    <step order="10">Update RB-T070-03 ledger: Status → `repaired` (path 1/2) or `archived-as-dead-target` (path 3); record chosen path in Notes + decision record `decisions/D-09-rb-t070-03-resolution.md`. Commit message reflects chosen mode: `fix(ai/chat): restore test seam in AnalysisChatContextResolver (RB-T070-03; repaired)` OR `test(ai/chat): archive AnalysisChatContextResolverTests as dead-target (RB-T070-03; archived-as-dead-target)`. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

